<div id="review_2552804710" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2552804710" />
    <a title="Justin Evans" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2184529-justin-evans"><img alt="Justin Evans" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1319658063p2/2184529.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2552804710?book_show_action=true">Oct 05, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Justin Evans" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Justin Evans" href="/user/show/2184529-justin-evans">Justin Evans</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2184529-justin-evans?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2552804710" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17010476106383070487">Perfectly... fine, in parts. Did we really need quite so much of it? No. Could I have done without most of the overt symbolism and so on? Yes. Does the structuralist-like analysis of the myths do anything for the book? No. Does it help me to understand the Joseph story in new and fascinating ways; does it have moments of true glory; can you skim huge chunks without missing anything of any importance whatsoever? Yes. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review2552804710">
  <td colspan="2">
    <div class="updateActionLinks">
        <a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link2552804710" title="Flag this review as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=2552804710&amp;resource_type=Review&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F88076.Joseph_and_His_Brothers">flag</a>





      <span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_review_2552804710'><a id="like_count_review_2552804710" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/2552804710?resource_type=Review"><span class="likesCount">5 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it gr-button gr-button--small" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F88076.Joseph_and_His_Brothers">Like</a></span>
&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a href="/review/show/2552804710?book_show_action=true&amp;from_review_page=1">see review</a>
    </div>


    <div id='comments_for_review_2552804710' style='display: none;'>
