<span id="freeTextContainer17365769194561955429">This is really a story of love and forgiveness. Joseph who doesn&apos;t know darkness, and is a light and loving soul wouldn&apos;t act any other way but to forgive his cunning brothers. Of course! However, is it his father to blame? If he loved all his children equally, would the history of the world still be the same?<br/></span>
  <span id="freeText17365769194561955429" style="display:none">This is really a story of love and forgiveness. Joseph who doesn't know darkness, and is a light and loving soul wouldn't act any other way but to forgive his cunning brothers. Of course! However, is it his father to blame? If he loved all his children equally, would the history of the world still be the same?<br /></span>
